# SDLC — Testing Phase

**Project:** {{PROJECT_NAME}} | **Stack:** {{LANGUAGE}} / {{FRAMEWORK}}
**Test command:** `{{TEST_CMD}}`

## Step 1 — Run the test suite

```bash
{{TEST_CMD}}
```

Report: total tests, passed, failed, skipped. If tests fail, stop and triage before continuing.

## Step 2 — Coverage analysis

Review coverage (if available). Identify untested code paths. Focus on:
- Business logic and domain rules
- Error handling branches
- Auth/authorisation checks
- Edge cases at input boundaries

## Step 3 — Test gap audit

For the feature or code area under review, verify these test types exist:

### Positive tests (happy path)
- [ ] Valid input → correct output
- [ ] Full user flow completes successfully

### Negative tests (required for every feature)
- [ ] Invalid input: null, empty, wrong type, too long, negative numbers, special characters
- [ ] Missing required fields
- [ ] Malformed requests (if API)
- [ ] Duplicate/idempotency violations

### Permission / auth tests
- [ ] Unauthenticated request returns 401 (or equivalent)
- [ ] Insufficient-role request returns 403 (or equivalent)
- [ ] User cannot access another user's data

### Boundary / edge-case tests
- [ ] Maximum allowed value
- [ ] Minimum allowed value
- [ ] Empty collection
- [ ] Single-item collection
- [ ] Concurrent duplicate requests (if applicable)

### Stress / load scenario (document, automate if tooling available)
- [ ] Expected load: __ req/sec, __ concurrent users
- [ ] Breaking point: __ req/sec before degradation
- [ ] Degradation behaviour: <describe expected graceful failure mode>

## Step 4 — Write missing tests

For each gap found in Step 3, write the missing test case using the project's test runner (`{{TEST_CMD}}`). Follow existing test file patterns exactly.

## Step 5 — Defect logging

For every defect found during testing:

```
ID: BUG-<N>
Title: <short description>
Severity: Critical / High / Medium / Low
Reproduction steps:
  1. <step>
  2. <step>
Expected: <what should happen>
Actual: <what happens>
Environment: <version, OS, browser if relevant>
```

Add to `.sdlc/defect-log.md` (create if absent).

## Step 6 — Test plan update

Update `.sdlc/test-plan.md` with:
- New test cases added this cycle
- Any test cases that were removed or changed
- Coverage delta (before vs. after)

## Step 7 — Release recommendation

Based on results:
- **Pass:** all critical/high tests pass, no open critical/high defects → ✅ Ready for deployment phase
- **Conditional pass:** medium defects only, workarounds exist → ⚠️ Document and proceed with PM approval
- **Fail:** any critical/high defect open → 🛑 Block release, return to implementation
